During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Chisenin|ja|智泉院 (東京都中央区)|lt=Chisenin|lt_ja=智泉院|qq=draft}} served as the head temple ({{ill|Bettō-ji|ja|別当寺|qq=draft}}) of this shrine; however, in the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代|qq=draft}}, due to the separation of Shinto and Buddhism ({{ill|Shinbutsu bunri|ja|神仏分離|qq=draft}}), it was detached from this shrine. Subsequently, with the elevation in status of the main Hie Shrine, this shrine was also reorganized.<ref name="日本橋摂社"></ref>

