'''Nihonbashi Hie Shrine''' (日枝神社日本橋摂社) is a {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine|qq=}} located in {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京都|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo|qq=}} {{ill|Chūō Ward, Tokyo|ja|中央区 (東京都)|lt=Chūō|lt_ja=中央区|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chūō Ward, Tokyo|qq=}} {{ill|Nihonbashi Kayabacho|ja|日本橋茅場町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihonbashi Kayabacho|qq=}}. It is the external {{ill|Sessha|ja|摂末社|lt=Sessha|lt_ja=摂社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sessha|qq=}} of the {{ill|Hie Shrine|ja|日枝神社 (千代田区)|lt=Hie Shrine|lt_ja=日枝神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hie Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Chiyoda Ward|ja|千代田区|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chiyoda Ward|qq=}} {{ill|Nagatachō|ja|永田町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagatachō|qq=}}.
It is also called '''Nihonbashi Hie Shrine'''.

==History==
In {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qq=}}18th year ({{ill|1590|ja|1590|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1590|qq=}}), following the entry of {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa Ieyasu|qq=}} into Edo, the {{ill|Portable Shrine|ja|神輿|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Portable Shrine|qq=}} of Hie Shrine was enshrined here. The location of the enshrinement is called {{ill|Otabi-sho|ja|御旅所|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otabi-sho|qq=}}. Even today, during the Sannō Festival held every other year, the portable shrine and {{ill|Dashi|ja|山車|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dashi|qq=}} make a tour between the main shrine and this shrine<ref name="日本橋摂社">[http://www.hiejinjanihombashisessha.tokyo/venerable.php Venerable history and enshrined deities] Nihonbashi Hie Shrine</ref>{{Sfn|Masayoshi Kanayama|Rumi Kanayama|1993|p=63}}.

During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo period|qq=}}, {{ill|Chisenin|ja|智泉院 (東京都中央区)|lt=Chisenin|lt_ja=智泉院|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chisenin|qq=}} served as the head temple ({{ill|Bettō-ji|ja|別当寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bettō-ji|qq=}}) of this shrine; however, in the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治|lt=Meiji period|1=Meiji era|2=ja|3=明治|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji period|qq=}}, due to the separation of Shinto and Buddhism ({{ill|Shinbutsu bunri|ja|神仏分離|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbutsu bunri|qq=}}), it was detached from this shrine. Subsequently, with the elevation in status of the main Hie Shrine, this shrine was also reorganized.<ref name="日本橋摂社"></ref>

==Access==
*{{ill|Kayabacho Station|ja|茅場町駅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kayabacho Station|qq=}} (1 minute walk).

